To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Open the BidiUtil class in the win32 platform.
2. Locate the line: static Callback callback = new Callback (Class.forName("com.sun.jna.Native"), "getWindowProc", 4);
3. Change the line above to: static Callback callback = new Callback (new BidiUtil().getClass(), "windowProc", 4);
4. Test if the software behaves the same way as before, but without using Class.forName().
